Class TDS

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.coreconsulting.res.openehr.tdd2canonical.util.XML
      • com.coreconsulting.res.openehr.tdd2canonical.TDS
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TDS
extends XML
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class implements functionality related to TDS handling, such as deserializing it from a XML instance, preloading the XPath expressions relevant to TDD transformation and resolving the @template_id.

    • Method Detail

      • loadNodeCache

        public void loadNodeCache()
        Preloads all relevant XPath expressions from the TDS into nodeCache, which acts as an in-memory cache, greatly optimizing node introspection/lookup during TDD transformation.

      • loadElementPaths

        public void loadElementPaths(org.w3c.dom.Element element,
                             java.lang.StringBuilder nodeXPath,
                             java.lang.StringBuilder xsdXPath)
        Load relevant XPath expressions from an element into nodeCache, which acts as an in-memory cache, greatly optimizing node introspection/lookup during TDD transformation. The algorithm is a postorder tree traversal, so it recursively traverses all descendants using the same path building scheme as the TDD transformation (see TDD.transformNode(Node, StringBuilder), so it loads any relevant attributes (@archetype_node_id, @type, @valueType) for every element that can be transformed.
        Parameters:
        element - current element being traversed
        nodeXPath - generic XPath for the current node in the TDS
        xsdXPath - XPath for the current node used during TDD transformation to look up a definition in the TDS

      • getCachedXPathAsString

        public java.lang.String getCachedXPathAsString(java.lang.String xpath)
        Runs a XPath expression on the TDS. Attempts to get the result from the nodeCache, in which it should be preloaded, but evaluates it with a performance warning otherwise.
        Parameters:
        xpath - XPath expression to be evaluated
        Returns:
        the result of the XPath evaluation, either from the nodeCache or evaluted online

      • getTemplateId

        public java.lang.String getTemplateId()
        Parses the @template_id from the TDS attribute definition. Once parsed, it is stored as a field for future use.
        Returns:
        @template_id from the TDD root element
